20mom.%20Moving%20back%20to%20the%20family%20farm%20was%20exactly%20what%20I%20needed.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221563%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Birthday%20party%20for%20two-year-old%20with%20family%20sitting%20around%20table%20eating%20cake.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fd201b2417f97b87ce4ca4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221172%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECat%20Jones%20is%20a%20single%20parent%20and%20moving%20into%20a%20multigenerational%20family%20home%20has%20been%20life-changing.%3Cp%3ECat%20Jones%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECat%20Jones%20eagerly%20left%20the%20family%20home%20at%2017%20and%20later%20bought%20a%20house%20230%20miles%20away%20with%20her%20husband.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20having%20a%20baby%20and%20leaving%20her%20husband%2C%20she%20was%20determined%20to%20make%20things%20work%20living%20on%20her%20own.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMoving%20back%20to%20her%20childhood%20home%20has%20felt%20like%20a%20massive%20burden%20was%20lifted%20off%20her%20shoulders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20a%20family%20with%20four%20girls%2C%20I%20always%20preferred%20my%20own%20space.%20When%20I%20was%2012%2C%20I%20chose%20to%20live%20in%20our%20converted%20garage%20instead%20of%20sleeping%20in%20the%20house.%20My%20free%20time%20was%20spent%20drawing%20or%20taking%20long%20walks%20in%20the%20countryside.%20Despite%20loving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-millennials-people-are-homesteading-control-uncontrollable-food-feel-safe-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elife%20on%20the%20farm%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20couldn't%20wait%20to%20spread%20my%20wings.%20So%2C%20at%2017%2C%20I%20left%20home.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20sisters%20and%20I%20have%20always%20taken%20advantage%20of%20the%20open-door%20policy%20at%20our%20parents'%20house%20in%20Tauranga%20%E2%80%94%20a%20city%20with%20a%20population%20of%20140%2C000%20people%20on%20the%20North%20Island%20of%20New%20Zealand.%20While%20I%20returned%20regularly%20to%20visit%2C%20I%20would%20never%20stay%20long.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20I%20got%20married%20and%20bought%20a%20house%20across%20the%20country%20%E2%80%93%20230%20miles%20away.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20was%20confident%20that%20it%20would%20be%20my%20forever%20home.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20my%20sisters%2C%20they%20all%20settled%20down%20nearby%20%E2%80%94%20my%20youngest%20still%20living%20at%20the%20family%20home%20and%20another%20right%20next%20door%20with%20her%20own%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20tried%20to%20live%20up%20to%20the%20single-parent%20superwoman%20ideal%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20giving%20birth%20to%20my%20daughter%20Cassie%2C%20my%20marriage%20fell%20apart%2C%20and%20I%20was%20left%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-divorced-husband-laid-off-happy-raising-daughter-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esingle%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20tight%20budget%20with%20no%20physical%20support.%20Fiercely%20independent%20and%20proud%2C%20I%20was%20determined%20to%20make%20things%20work%20on%20my%20own.%20And%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20it%20did%20work.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20remodeling%20my%20house%2C%20made%20new%20friends%2C%20and%20focused%20on%20raising%20Cassie.%20I%20relished%20our%20relaxed%20schedule%3B%20waking%2C%20eating%2C%20playing%2C%20and%20napping%20in%20tune%20with%20our%20needs%2C%20not%20society's%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mother%20reading%20a%20book%20on%20coach%20with%20baby%20laying%20on%20her.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fd293b2417f97b87ce4cb8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20and%20her%20daughter%20were%20living%20on%20their%20own%20and%20not%20interacting%20with%20other%20people%20enough.%3Cp%3ECat%20Jones%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20something%20was%20missing.%20My%20baby%20memorized%20her%20first%20book%20at%20six%20months.%20By%20the%20time%20she%20turned%20one%2C%20she%20knew%20which%20stories%20were%20associated%20with%20each%20picture%20in%20her%20nursery%20rhyme%20book%20and%20would%20eagerly%20babble%20at%20me%20to%20read%20her%20favorite%20rhymes.%20So%20when%20Cassie%20didn't%20start%20talking%20early%2C%20or%20even%20in%20line%20with%20other%20children%20her%20age%2C%20worry%20set%20in.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20to%20realize%20what%20was%20missing%20from%20our%20life%3A%20people.%20Some%20days%20we%20saw%20friends%20and%20acquaintances%20for%20an%20hour%20or%20so%2C%20but%20most%20days%20were%20filled%20with%20one-sided%20conversations%20with%20my%20baby.%20There%20were%20days%20when%20I%20barely%20spoke%20at%20all.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20had%20to%20change.%20After%20an%20extended%20trip%20back%20to%20the%20farm%2C%20surrounded%20by%20family%20and%20endless%20chatter%2C%20Cassie%20was%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20talking%20when%20we%20left.%20I%20knew%20the%20solution%20to%20our%20solitude%20was%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmultigenerational-homebuying-rises-pandemic-changes-american-family-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emove%20back%20to%20the%20family%20home%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222491%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Young%20girl%20playing%20with%20calf%20on%20a%20farm%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fd2a95895d8220303331c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221868%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20a%20trip%20home%20to%20visit%20family%20at%20the%20farm%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20things%20had%20to%20change.%3Cp%3ECat%20Jones%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EHaving%20a%20child%20in%20a%20household%20of%20adults%20brings%20everyone%20joy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20being%20joined%20at%20the%20hip%20when%20living%20alone%2C%20it's%20now%20common%20for%20me%20to%20not%20know%20where%20my%20now%20two-year-old%20daughter%20is%20as%20she%20goes%20about%20her%20own%20life.%20On%20any%20given%20day%2C%20Cassie%20can%20be%20found%20helping%20her%20aunts%20feed%20horses%2C%20playing%20outside%20with%20the%20dogs%2C%20bringing%20the%20cows%20in%20for%20milking%20with%20her%20granddad%20or%20reading%20a%20book%20with%20her%20grandma.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFarm%20life%20is%20notoriously%20stressful%20and%20persistent.%20Tired%20and%20grumpy%20parents%20have%20become%20the%20norm%20over%20the%20years.%20Now%20things%20are%20different.%20Cassie%20has%20a%20vivaciousness%20about%20life%2C%20dancing%20places%20instead%20of%20walking%2C%20and%20singing%20at%20any%20opportunity.%20Her%20attitude%20is%20infectious%20and%20has%20made%20a%20remarkable%20change%20in%20all%20of%20the%20adults%20on%20the%20farm.%20It's%20hard%20to%20be%20stressed%20when%20a%20child%20is%20ready%20to%20share%20her%20toys%20and%20offer%20cuddles.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20I%20am%20the%20provider%20for%20my%20daughter%2C%20the%20responsibility%20of%20raising%20a%20child%20is%20removed%20from%20everyone%20else%2C%20leaving%20only%20the%20joy%20of%20watching%20a%20young%20life%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt%20works%20for%20us%2C%20but%20it%20might%20not%20be%20for%20everyone%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20found%20a%20safe%20haven%20by%20moving%20back%20to%20my%20childhood%20home%2C%20but%20it%20took%20a%20while%20to%20make%20it%20work.%20There%20are%20trade-offs%2C%20and%20it%20takes%20a%20group%20effort%20to%20create%20a%20positive%20environment.%20Living%20in%20such%20close%20quarters%20with%20other%20adults%20requires%20communication%2C%20understanding%2C%20and%20patience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20arrived%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20be%20helpful%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-decor-tips-moving-in-husband-wife-house-blended-family-2023-10%5C%22%20t