d%20by%20video%2C%20the%20New%20Yorker%20was%20disappointed%20to%20learn%20she%20wasn't%20moving%20to%20the%20next%20round.%20When%20Weaver%20asked%20for%20feedback%2C%20the%20recruiter%20replied%20in%20an%20email%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%20that%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bconcerned%20that%20you%20didn't%20put%20forth%20enough%20effort%20into%20your%20appearance%20given%20you%20were%20interviewing%20for%20a%20Vice%20President%20role.%26quot%3B%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20brevity%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20my%20previous%20job%20in%20December.%20When%20I%20started%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20job%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20it%20would%20be%20one%20where%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20could%20contribute%20a%20lot.%20I%20found%20a%20posting%20on%20LinkedIn%20for%20a%20vice%20president%20of%20human%20resources%20role%2C%20which%20I%20understand%20is%20ironic%2C%20given%20what%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20looked%20at%20the%20job%20description%20and%20knew%20it%20was%20in%20line%20with%20what%20I%20had%20done%20previously.%20I%20researched%20the%20company%20and%20their%20core%20values%2C%20which%2C%20again%20%E2%80%94%20very%20ironic.%20Then%20I%20applied.%20The%20recruiter%20reached%20out%20and%20said%20that%20my%20background%20aligned%20with%20what%20they%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interview%20was%20by%20video.%20I%20had%20on%20a%20black%20blazer%20and%20a%20collared%20shirt%2C%20both%20of%20which%20were%20ironed.%20I%20wore%20small%20gold%20earrings.%20I'd%20done%20a%20blowout%20on%20my%20hair%20and%20had%20beige-colored%20nails.%20I%20did%20everything%20in%20line%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-colors-to-wear-job-interview-color-psychologist-expert-2024-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBusiness%2520Insider%2520asked%2520two%2520color%2Cyou%2520need%2520some%2520extra%2520encouragement.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproper%20professional%20attire%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20I%20didn't%20wear%20makeup%2C%20which%20I%20didn't%20think%20was%20a%20big%20deal.%20But%20apparently%2C%20it%20was%20to%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20the%20interview%20went%20really%20well.%20I%20had%20good%20answers%20to%20questions.%20Having%20a%20recruitment%20background%2C%20I%20know%20how%20to%20have%20conversations%20with%20people.%20It%20was%20supposed%20to%20go%2030%20minutes%2C%20but%20it%20went%20closer%20to%2040.%20I%20was%20really%20optimistic%20when%20the%20call%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EConcerns%20about%20my%20appearance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20days%20after%20the%20interview%2C%20I%20got%20an%20email%20from%20the%20recruiter%20saying%20that%20I%20was%20in%20line%20with%20what%20they%20wanted%20in%20terms%20of%20experience%20and%20that%20my%20values%20aligned%20with%20theirs%20but%20that%20they%20wouldn't%20be%20moving%20forward.%20I%20decided%20to%20ask%20for%20feedback.%20She%20wrote%20back%20and%20said%20she%20was%20concerned%20that%20I%20didn't%20put%20enough%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiter-linkedin-tiktok-job-interview-outfits-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeffort%20into%20my%20appearance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20reaction%20was%20a%20bit%20of%20shock.%20One%2C%20that%20someone%20would%20write%20that%20in%20an%20email.%20But%20more%20so%2C%20that%20in%202024%2C%20this%20is%20still%20happening.%20I%20had%20so%20much%20enthusiasm%20about%20the%20company%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20I%20was%20good%20for%20the%20role.%20I%20can%20only%20assume%20her%20concern%20was%20that%20I%20didn't%20put%20on%20makeup%20because%20I'd%20done%20everything%20else.%20So%20hearing%20that%20because%20I%20hadn't%20done%20that%2C%20I%20was%20somehow%20less%20qualified%20or%20didn't%20seem%20like%20I%20was%20as%20enthusiastic%20about%20the%20job%20was%20just%20baffling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20tend%20to%20wear%20that%20much%20makeup%20for%20various%20reasons.%20One%2C%20makeup%20is%20so%20expensive.%20There's%20a%20reason%20cosmetics%20is%20a%20billion-dollar%20industry.%20It's%20also%20just%20not%20something%20that%20I%20enjoy%20doing.%20I%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20friends%20who%20are%20happy%20to%20spend%2045%20minutes%20to%20an%20hour%20on%20their%20makeup.%20It's%20their%20zen%20time.%20Props%20to%20them%2C%20but%20I'd%20rather%20invest%20in%20my%20skincare.%20My%20dermatologist%20and%20I%20are%20on%20a%20first-name%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20South%20in%20a%20culture%20of%20you%20have%20to%20put%20your%20face%20on%20to%20just%20go%20to%20the%20grocery%20store.%20My%20mom%20and%20I%20joked%20that%20there%20are%20probably%20women%20whose%20significant%20others%20have%20never%20seen%20them%20without%20a%20full%20face%20of%20makeup.%20At%20night%2C%20they'd%20take%20off%20their%20makeup%20and%20put%20on%20a%20fresh%20face%20of%20it%20just%20to%20go%20to%20bed.%20To%20each%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20dressed%20up.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20comments%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40_melissaweaver%2Fvideo%2F7346698157536922910%3F_t%3D8ktMty4EY6U%26_r%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%20I%20made%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20experience%2C%20people%20say%20things%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20actually%20heard%20that%20I've%20worn%20too%20much%20makeup%20in%20my%20interview.%26quot%3B%20Or%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20supposed%20to%20wear%20red%20lipstick%20because%20it's%20too%20much%20of%20a%20power%20move.%26quot%3B%20One%20woman%20said%20she%20got%20more%20assignments%20at%20work%20when%20she%20started%20wearing%20makeup.%20For%20someone%20else%2C%20it%20was%20losing%20weight.%20Reading%20that%20%E2%80%94%20in%202024%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0our%20appearance%20somehow%20correlates%20to%20our%20ability%20to%20do%20our%20jobs%20is%20very%20disheartening.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20use%20makeup%20to%20enhance%20their%20features.%20But%20the%20idea%20that%20that's%20a%20requirement%20is%20kind%20of%20insane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20dressed%20up%20for%20the%20interview.%20Dressing%20nicely%20shows%20that%20you%20have%20enthusiasm%20for%20the%20job%20and%20take%20it%20seriously.%20That%20applies%20to%20both%20men%20and%20women.%20So%2C%20in%20recruitment%2C%20I%20never%20judged%20someone%20if%20they%20wore%20makeup%20or%20if%20a%20man%20had%20long%20hair%2C%20as%20long%20as%20it%20was%20well-kept.%20I%20did%20have%20someone%20show%20up%20in%20a%20video%20interview%20in%20pajamas%20once.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20really%20sure%20about%20this%20for%20a%20senior-level%20position.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20is%2C%20makeup%20just%20applies%20to%20women.%20It's%20not%20expected%20that%20men%20wear%20foundation%20or%20contour%20or%20whatever.%20But%20that%20something%20gender-specific%20can%20somehow%20impact%20a%20role%20is%20not%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20might%20have%20been%20more%20shocking%20had%20the%20comment%20come%20from%20a%20man%20because%2C%20having%20worked%20in%20recruitment%2C%20I%20never%20had%20a%20male%20colleague%20comment%20about%20a%20woman's%20makeup.%20Maybe%2C%20for%20women%2C%20it's%20a%20matter%20of%20them%20wearing%20it%20themselves%20so%20they%20would%20expect%20it%20from%20another%20woman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20this%20experience%20is%20necessarily%20going%20to%20change%20my%20approach%20to%20a%20job%20search%20because%20I%20want%20to%20be%20part%20of%20a%20company%20that%20has%20a%20supportive%20culture%20and%20that%20doesn't%20have%20the%20sort%20of%20expectations%20of%20women%20having%20to%20wear%20makeup.%20Making%20sure%20that%20companies%20have%20an%20inclusive%20culture%20is%20incredibly%20important%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERecruiters%20are%20the%20face%20of%20a%20company.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20it's%20necessarily%20fair%20to%20judge%20an%20entire%20company%20based%20on%20one%20person%2C%20though%20recruiters%20are%20typically%20the%20face%20of%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20or%20the%20first%20face%20you%20see.%20So%20that's%20something%20to%20be%20mindful%20of.%20I%20don't%20think%20I%20could%20learn%20all%20I%20want%20to%20know%20about%20a%20company's%20culture%20based%20on%20the%20first%20person%20that%20I%20meet%20with%20or%20even%20the%20first%20few%20people.%20That's%20why%20I%20appreciate%20a%20hiring%20process%20with%20multiple%20interviews%20with%20different%20people.%20As%20draining%20as%20some%20people%20can%20find%20that%2C%20I%20appreciate%20it%20because%20you%20do%20get%20a%20feel%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20different%20people%20in%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20I've%20always%20loved%20about%20being%20an%20HR%20is%20that%20it%20is%20a%20people-facing%20role.%20That's%20why%20I%20want%20to%20find%20an%20employer%20with%20an%20inclusive%20culture%20and%20where%20I%20can%20contribute%20to%20that.%20This%20is%20about%20women%20supporting%20women%20and%20men%20supporting%20women%20as%20well.%20It's%20given%20me%20an%20extra%20boost%20in%20terms%20of%20knowing%20what%20I'm%20passionate%20about%2C%20which%20I%20want%20to%20be%20sure%20I%20can%20bring%20to%20a%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20write%20the%20recruiter%20back%20because%20I%20didn't%20think%20it%20would%20make%20a%20difference.%20Several%20people%20encouraged%20me%20to%20forward%20her%20email%20to%20the%20company's%20head%20of%20HR.%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20I%20will.%20You%20also%20worry%20about%20being%20blackballed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHR%20can%20be%20taxing%20work%2C%20but%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20I%20love%20it.%20I%20love%20working%20with%20people.%20And%20so%20I%20know%20that%20it's%20the%20lane%20that%20I%20want%20to%20stay%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20make%20the%20TikTok%20to%20bash%20the%20company%20or%20anything%20like%20that.%20I%20never%20wanted%20it%20to%20be%20a%20crusade.%20I%20just%20wanted%20people's%20opinions%2C%20and%20if%20it%2