idating%20when%20people%20%E2%80%94%20doctors%20%E2%80%94%20were%20blowing%20off%20my%20concerns%20as%20soon%20as%20they%20heard%20I%20was%20a%20new%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%203%20cancer%2C%20and%20needed%20fertility%20treatments%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20I%20found%20a%20doctor%20who%20took%20me%20seriously%20and%20ordered%20a%20colonoscopy.%20Shortly%20after%20I%20saw%20a%20specialist%20at%20Memorial%20Sloan%20Kettering%20Cancer%20Center%20who%20diagnosed%20me%20with%20stage%203%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-young-adults-signs-symptoms-risk-quiz-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolorectal%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Jayce%20was%208%20months%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20was%20I%20facing%20a%20terrifying%20diagnosis%2C%20but%20the%20doctor%20immediately%20started%20talking%20about%20my%20fertility.%20I%20was%20only%2028%2C%20but%20the%20protocol%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeing-organized-helped-me-through-my-cancer-diagnosis-and-treatment-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echemotherapy%2C%20radiation%2C%20and%20surgery%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20likely%20leave%20me%20unable%20to%20conceive.%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20more%20kids%2C%20but%20talking%20about%20fertility%20right%20after%20being%20diagnosed%20with%20cancer%20was%20overwhelming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20pummeled%20physically%2C%20mentally%2C%20emotionally%2C%20and%20financially.%20And%20this%20hadn't%20even%20really%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAt%20the%20last%20minute%2C%20I%20chose%20a%20clinical%20trial%20that%20could%20preserve%20my%20fertility%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20doctor's%20advice%2C%20I%20underwent%20fertility%20treatments%20and%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshould-i-freeze-my-eggs-2017-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eegg%20retrieval%3C%2Fa%3E%20soon%20after%20I%20was%20diagnosed%20and%20before%20treatment%20started.%20That%20was%20truly%20the%20worst%20part%20of%20this%20experience.%20Having%20swollen%2C%20bloated%20ovaries%20near%20my%20tumor%20was%20incredibly%20painful.%20But%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20ended%20up%20with%20four%20embryos%20%E2%80%94%20hope%20for%20the%20future%20family%20we%20envisioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20day%20I%20was%20set%20to%20begin%20treatment%2C%20a%20research%20nurse%20came%20in%20and%20explained%20I%20was%20eligible%20for%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstanduptocancer.org%2Fresearch%2Fresearch-portfolio%2Fdream-teams%2Fcolorectal-cancer-vulnerabilities-dream-team%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20clinical%20trial%3C%2Fa%3E%20run%20by%20Stand%20Up%20to%20Cancer%20and%20Memorial%20Sloan%20Kettering%20Cancer%20Center.%20It%20would%20use%20immunotherapy%20to%20treat%20colorectal%20cancer.%20Only%20three%20other%20people%20had%20the%20treatment.%20If%20it%20worked%2C%20it%20could%20cure%20my%20cancer%20while%20preserving%20my%20fertility.%20If%20I%20didn't%2C%20we'd%20go%20back%20to%20the%20typical%20treatment%20plan%20of%20chemo%2C%20radiation%2C%20and%20surgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20said%20yes%20right%20away.%20By%20the%20second%20treatment%2C%20I%20was%20feeling%20so%20much%20better.%20By%20the%20ninth%20and%20final%20treatment%2C%20my%20tumor%20was%20gone.%20In%20August%2C%20I%20learned%20I%20wouldn't%20need%20radiation%20or%20surgery%20because%20I%20didn't%20have%20cancer%20anymore.%20That%20was%20the%20best%20day%20of%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20got%20pregnant%20using%20the%20embryos%20I%20created%20before%20treatment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20get%20pregnant%20immediately.%20I%20left%20an%20appointment%20in%20tears%20after%20doctors%20explained%20I%20should%20wait%20two%20years%20while%20I%20was%20at%20the%20highest%20risk%20of%20relapse.%20I%20used%20those%20two%20years%20to%20process%20everything%20that%20had%20happened%20to%20me%3A%20becoming%20a%20mom%2C%20cancer%20patient%2C%20then%20survivor%20all%20at%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20cleared%20to%20get%20pregnant%2C%20I%20knew%20we%20could%20try%20to%20conceive%20naturally.%20Yet%20I%20had%20worked%20so%20hard%20for%20those%20embryos%20I%20was%20determined%20to%20use%20them.%20That%20led%20to%20my%20daughter%2C%20Maya%2C%20who%20was%20born%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20more%20kids%20in%20the%20future%2C%20and%20I%20would%20like%20to%20try%20to%20get%20pregnant%20the%20old-fashioned%20way.%20I'm%20so%20incredibly%20grateful%20for%20the%20nurse%20who%20told%20me%20to%20advocate%20for%20myself%2C%20the%20doctor%20who%20guided%20me%20to%20fertility%20treatments%2C%20and%20the%20research%20nurse%20who%20connected%20me%20with%20the%20clinical%20trial.%20They%20saved%20not%20only%20me%20but%20my%20family%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbloody-stool-pregnancy-hemorrhoids-colorectal-cancer-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711277281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e796be6080194819fcdaa5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbloody-stool-pregnancy-hemorrhoids-colorectal-cancer-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kelly%20Spill%20had%20bloody%20stool%20during%20pregnancy%20and%20figured%20it%20was%20due%20to%20hemorrhoids.%20She%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20colorectal%20cancer%20after%20her%20son's%20birth.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kelly%20Burch)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbloody-stool-pregnancy-hemorrhoids-colorectal-cancer-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pope%20skips%20Palm%20Sunday%20homily%20but%20continues%20service%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711276853000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108749805%2Cimgsize-1194650.