r%20the%20late%20patriarch%20of%20their%20family%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0Danny's%20father%2C%20Al%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0there%20would%20be%20no%20Israeli%20Air%20Force%2C%20or%20perhaps%20even%20an%20Israel.%20As%20the%20country's%20founder%20and%20first%20prime%20minister%2C%20David%20Ben-Gurion%2C%20once%20declared%2C%20%26quot%3BAmerica's%20greatest%20gift%20to%20Israel%20was%20Al%20Schwimmer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20decorated%20World%20War%20II%20veteran%20from%20Connecticut%2C%20Schwimmer%20was%20Israel's%20most%20notorious%20arms%20smuggler.%20In%201948%2C%20as%20Jews%20were%20fighting%20to%20carve%20a%20homeland%20for%20themselves%20out%20of%20Arab%20territory%2C%20he%20masterminded%20a%20covert%2C%20illegal%2C%20international%20operation%20that%20was%20equal%20parts%20%26quot%3BArgo%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BMission%20Impossible.%26quot%3B%20Working%20with%20the%20Jewish%20underground%20paramilitary%2C%20the%20Haganah%2C%20Schwimmer%20led%20a%20team%20of%20World%20War%20II%20veterans%20to%20break%20an%20American%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eembargo%20and%20smuggle%20125%20military%20planes%20and%20more%20than%2050%2C000%20weapons%20to%20Palestine.%20They%20were%20supported%20in%20the%20campaign%20by%20a%20diverse%20and%20unlikely%20gang%20of%20volunteers%2C%20including%20Bugsy%20Siegel's%20publicist%2C%20the%20mobster%20Meyer%20Lansky%2C%20Pee-wee%20Herman's%20father%2C%20and%20Frank%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpost.com%2Fj-spot%2Farticle-710941%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESinatra%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20young%20nation%2C%26quot%3B%20Sinatra%20later%20explained.%20%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20to%20help.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222352%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%201959%2C%20Al%20Schwimmer%20shows%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20David%20Ben-Gurion%20a%20jet%20built%20by%20Israel%20Aircraft%20Industries.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fb2fad2417f97b87cdd21c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222355%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAl%20Schwimmer%20with%20David%20Ben-Gurion%2C%20prime%20minister%20of%20Israel%2C%20in%201959.%20The%20planes%20Schwimmer%20smuggled%20%E2%80%94%20and%20built%20%E2%80%94%20created%20Israel's%20air%20force.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Boaz%20Dvir%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aid%20made%20Schwimmer%20a%20hero%20in%20Israel%20%E2%80%94%20and%20an%20outlaw%20at%20home.%20%26quot%3BAll%20the%20time%20the%20FBI%20was%20knocking%20on%20their%20door%2C%26quot%3B%20Danny%20recalls.%20Convicted%20of%20violating%20the%20Neutrality%20Act%2C%20Schwimmer%20was%20stripped%20of%20his%20voting%20rights%20and%20his%20veterans%20benefits%2C%20becoming%20a%20second-class%20citizen%20in%20the%20nation%20he%20had%20gone%20to%20war%20to%20defend.%20So%20he%20immigrated%20to%20the%20country%20he%20had%20helped%20create%2C%20playing%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20building%20Israel's%20airline%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimmer%2C%20who%20died%20in%202011%2C%20seldom%20discussed%20his%20story%20in%20public.%20But%20I%20was%20in%20a%20unique%20position%20to%20hear%20it%20firsthand.%20Thirty%20years%20ago%20I%20married%20into%20the%20Schwimmer%20family%2C%20and%20I%20spent%20many%20Thanksgivings%20talking%20to%20%26quot%3BUncle%20Al.%26quot%3B%20With%20wispy%20white%20hair%20and%20precocious%20eyes%2C%20he%20was%20wry%2C%20quiet%2C%20and%20extremely%20modest%20about%20what%20he'd%20done.%20He%20was%20also%2C%20as%20I%20later%20discovered%2C%20a%20man%20with%20plenty%20to%20hide%2C%20and%20a%20guilt%20that%20hounded%20him%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20years%20since%20his%20death%2C%20I've%20been%20talking%20to%20his%20son%2C%20Danny%2C%20and%20his%20widow%2C%20Rina%2C%20who%20provided%20me%20with%20access%20to%20his%20personal%20writings.%20Schwimmer's%20smuggling%20partner%2C%20Hank%20Greenspun%2C%20was%20especially%20eager%20to%20share%20the%20tale%20of%20his%20friend's%20exploits.%20On%20his%20deathbed%20in%201989%2C%20Greenspun%20asked%20his%20son%2C%20Brian%2C%20to%20let%20the%20world%20know%20what%20Schwimmer%20had%20accomplished%20on%20behalf%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20was%20trying%20to%20make%20sure%20people%20knew%20what%20it%20took%20to%20birth%20a%20country%20and%20to%20help%20it%20grow%2C%26quot%3B%20Brian%20recalls%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20what%20kind%20of%20people%20it%20took%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%20in%20April%201947%2C%20Adolph%20%26quot%3BAl%26quot%3B%20Schwimmer%20visited%20Hotel%20Fourteen%2C%20home%20to%20New%20York%20City's%20hottest%20nightclub%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nydailynews.com%2F2022%2F02%2F11%2Flook-back-at-copacabanas-75-years-as-nyc-hotspot%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECopacabana%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Still%20wearing%20his%20uniform%20as%20a%20TWA%20flight%20engineer%2C%20the%2029-year-old%20had%20rushed%20to%20the%20hotel%20during%20a%20layover.%20But%20Schwimmer%2C%20who%20walked%20with%20a%20limp%2C%20hadn't%20come%20to%20enjoy%20the%20club.%20Instead%20he%20knocked%2C%20unannounced%2C%20on%20the%20door%20of%20an%20office%20listed%20in%20the%20hotel's%20business%20directory%20with%20two%20innocent%20words%3A%20%3Cem%3EJaffa%20Oranges%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20was%20the%20secret%20headquarters%20of%20the%20Haganah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20a%20crisis%20was%20mounting%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20The%20British%20were%20preparing%20to%20turn%20over%20control%20of%20Palestine%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20and%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20Holocaust%20refugees%20were%20attempting%20to%20resettle%20in%20the%20Holy%20Land.%20With%20the%20Arabs%20who%20lived%20there%20determined%20to%20defend%20themselves%20against%20what%20they%20saw%20as%20an%20invasion%2C%20war%20seemed%20inevitable.%20But%20Jews%20had%20few%20arms%2C%20let%20alone%20an%20organized%20military%2C%20and%20the%20United%20States%20had%20placed%20strict%20limits%20on%20arms%20exports.%20To%20circumvent%20the%20law%2C%20the%20Haganah%20had%20set%20up%20offices%20in%20Hotel%20Fourteen%2C%20working%20with%20American%20volunteers%20to%20smuggle%20arms%20to%20Palestine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimmer%20told%20me%20he%20felt%20a%20moral%20obligation%20to%20help.%20In%20the%20days%20after%20World%20War%20II%2C%20while%20he%20was%20working%20for%20TWA%2C%20his%20mother%20had%20asked%20him%20to%20find%20out%20what%20had%20happened%20to%20her%20parents%20and%20her%20siblings.%20Schwimmer%20journeyed%20to%20the%20family's%20village%20in%20Hungary%2C%20where%20he%20found%20a%20fresh%20monument%20in%20the%20Jewish%20cemetery.%20It%20listed%20the%20names%20of%20the%20many%20residents%20who%20had%20been%20murdered%20in%20Auschwitz%2C%20including%20his%20mother's%20entire%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimmer%20decided%20never%20to%20share%20what%20he%20had%20learned%20with%20his%20mother%2C%20out%20of%20a%20desire%20to%20protect%20her.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20tell%20ma%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20later%20told%20Rina.%20%26quot%3BIt'll%20break%20her.%26quot%3B%20But%20he%20never%20forgot%2C%20and%20when%20he%20saw%20how%20Holocaust%20survivors%20were%20flocking%20to%20Palestine%2C%20he%20snapped%20into%20action.%20%26quot%3BPlanes%20were%20needed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20where%20I%20came%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20self-described%20%26quot%3Bquiet%2C%20puny%20teenager%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimmer%20had%20long%20dreamed%20of%20being%20a%20pilot.%20But%20after%20a%20football%20injury%20required%20part%20of%20his%20left%20leg%20to%20be%20amputated%2C%20he%20focused%20on%20building%20planes%20instead%20of%20flying%20them%20%E2%80%94%20starting%20with%20a%20rudimentary%20one%20he%20pieced%20together%20in%20his%20backyard%20in%20Connecticut.%20%26quot%3BAll%20throughout%20my%20teen%20years%20I%20had%20to%20prove%20to%20myself%20and%20to%20others%20that%20I%20was%20strong%2C%20despite%20a%20damaged%20leg%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20later%20recalled.%20After%20dropping%20out%20of%20high%20school%20to%20support%20his%20impoverished%20family%2C%20he%20went%20to%20work%20as%20a%20flight%20engineer.%20During%20the%20war%20he%20earned%20a%20medal%20for%20extinguishing%20an%20engine%20fire%20mid-flight.%20His%20friends%20took%20to%20calling%20him%20Wing%20Walker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20with%20the%20war%20over%2C%20Schwimmer%20knew%20America%20had%20all%20the%20planes%20the%20Jews%20in%20Palestine%20would%20need%20%E2%80%94%20if%20he%20could%20get%20his%20hands%20on%20them.%20%26quot%3BSurplus%20planes%20were%20scattered%20in%20airport%20storages%2C%20depots%2C%20and%20literally%20strewn%20all%20over%20the%20Arizona%20desert%2C%20as%20far%20as%20the%20eye%20could%20see%20%E2%80%A6%20rotting%20under%20the%20hot%20sun%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20he%20put%20it.%20That's%20why%20he%20had%20showed%20up%20at%20the%20Haganah's%20office%20at%20Hotel%20Fourteen%2C%20after%20another%20veteran%20had%20given%20him%20the%20address.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20the%20man%20they%20could%20count%20on%20to%20do%20everything%20possible%20to%20acquire%20the%20appropriate%20transport%20planes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled.%20The%20prospect%20of%20working%20as%20a%20secret%20agent%20would%20also%20fulfill%20a%20boyhood%20fantasy%20spurred%20by%20a%20Sunday%20comic%20strip%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20captivated%20by%20the%20image%20of%20Dick%20Tracy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EJoining%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jewishvirtuallibrary.org%2Fthe-haganah%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Haganah%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Schwimmer%20discovered%2C%20wasn't%20as%20easy%20as%20just%20strolling%20through%20the%20door.%20Given%20the%20illegality%20of%20the%20operation%20and%20the%20need%20for%20secrecy%2C%20the%20underground%20group%20wasn't%20going%20to%20let%20some%20walk-in%20join%20its%20smuggling%20ring.%20They%20would%20check%20into%20Schwimmer%2C%20they%20told%20him%2C%20and%20let%20him%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%2C%20a%20Haganah%20agent%20showed%20up%20at%20the%20family's%20home%20in%20Bridgeport%20and%20started%20asking%20questions.%20Schwimmer's%20mother%2C%20whose%20family%20had%20vanished%20in%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20was%20terrified.%20%26quot%3BHis%20mother%20got%20very%20frightened%2C%26quot%3B%20Rina%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BShe%20told%20him%20her%20son%20was%20in%20the%20country.%20She%20was%20very%2C%20very%20antagonistic%20to%20this%20guy%20coming%20to%20check%20on%20her.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20Schwimmer%20passed%20the%20background%20check%2C%20the%20Haganah%20sent%20him%20on%20a%20trial%20mission%3A%20to%20deliver%20sensitive%20files%20to%20agents%20in%20Rome.%20Using%20his%20job%20as%20a%20TWA%20flight%20engineer%20as%20cover%2C%20Schwimmer%20arranged%20for%20drop-offs%20during%20his%20layovers.%20After%20several%20successful%20runs%2C%20he%20was%20introduced%20to%20the%20new%20leader%20of%20the%20Haganah%2C%20Yehuda%20Arazi.%20Known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BKing%20of%20Ruses%26quot%3B%20for%20his%20chameleon-like%20disguises%2C%20Arazi%20had%20been%20in%20hiding%20since%20stealing%20thousands%20of%20rifles%20from%20the%20British.%20Together%2C%20the%20two%20men%20developed%20an%20outrageous%20plan.%20The%20US%20government%2C%20Schwimmer%20knew%2C%20was%20selling%20surplus%20planes%20from%20the%20war%20at%20drastically%20discounted%20rates.%20With%20money%20from%20the%20Haganah%2C%20he%20could%20buy%20the%20planes%20and%20recruit%20his%20old%20war%20buddies%20to%20smuggle%20them%20to%20the%20Jews%20in%20Palestine%2C%20circumventing%20the%20American%20ban%20on%20unlicensed%20arms%20exports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20all%20Schwimmer%20needed%20was%20a%20convincing%20cover.%20Armed%20with%20cash%20from%20the%20Haganah%2C%20he%20opened%20a%20hangar%20for%20a%20new%20commercial%20airline%20%E2%80%94%20Schwimmer%20Aviation%20%E2%80%94%20at%20the%20Lockheed%20Air%20Terminal%20in%20Burbank%2C%20California.%20Then%2C%20using%20the%20hangar%20as%20a%20hub%20for%20the%20operation%2C%20he%20purchased%20several%20surplus%20warplanes%20and%20flew%20them%20to%20Burbank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22953%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%201948%2C%20Al%20Schwimmer%20(second%20from%20right)%20speaks%20with%20his%20chief%20mechanic%2C%20Willie%20Sosnow%20(right)%2C%20at%20the%20Lockheed%20Air%20Terminal%20in%20Burbank%2C%20Calif.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fb3159895d82203032ba74%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22593%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESchwimmer%20(second%20from%20right)%20at%20Lockheed%20Air%20Terminal%20in%20Burbank%2C%20the%20base%20for%20his%20smuggling%20operation.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Boaz%20Dvir%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20recruit%20pilots%20and%20mechanics%20to%20the%20cause%2C%20he%20reached%20out%20to%20his%20fellow%20veterans.%20Many%20refused%20to%20help.%20%26quot%3BThey%20thought%20they'd%20slipped%20on%20their%20heads%2C%26quot%3B%20recalled%20Danny%2C%20Schwimmer's%20son.%20%26quot%3BThey'd%20just%20come%20back%20from%20World%20War%20II%2C%20and%20here%20they're%20going%20to%20go%20and%20risk%20their%20lives%20in%20a%20war%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20world%3F%20Jews%20in%20the%20United%20States%20were%20not%20that%20enthusiastic%20to%20go%20die%20for%20the%20Jewish%20state.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20by%20one%2C%20Schwimmer%20found%20vets%20who%20were%20willing%20to%20take%20the%20risk.%20Sam%20Lewis%2C%20the%20son%20of%20a%20Yiddish%20poet%2C%20had%20trained%20pilots%20in%20combat%20aerobatics%20during%20the%20war.%20His%20friend%20Leo%20Gardner%20was%20renowned%20as%20a%20flying%20ace.%20Milton%20%26quot%3BMilt%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Few.com%2Farticle%2F2015%2F04%2F28%2Fpaul-reubens-father-above-and-beyond-doc%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERubenfeld%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whose%20son%20Paul%20Reubens%20would%20later%20become%20better%20known%20as%20Pee-wee%20Herman%2C%20was%20a%20stunt-turned-fighter%20pilot.%20Like%20Schwimmer%2C%20Rubenfeld%20was%20modest%20about%20his%20involvement%20in%20the%20secret%20operation.%20%26quot%3BMy%20father%20didn't%20like%20to%20talk%20about%20his%20many%20accomplishments%2C%26quot%3B%20Reubens%20once%20said.%20But%20Rubenfeld%2C%20along%20with%20the%20others%2C%20joined%20on%20one%20condition.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20only%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20Danny%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwas%20that%20their%20families%20be%20taken%20care%20of%20when%20they%20were%20away%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20assuming%20they%20made%20it%20back%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20was%20one%20crucial%20role%20remaining%20to%20be%20filled%3A%20a%20weapons%20expert.%20Schwimmer%20needed%20someone%20not%20only%20with%20a%20knowledge%20of%20munitions%2C%20but%20with%20the%20nerve%20to%20find%20and%20smuggle%20them%20to%20Palestine.%20One%20of%20the%20veterans%20who%20joined%20the%20group%20said%20he%20had%20just%20the%20guy.%20So%20Schwimmer%20flew%20to%20Las%20Vegas%20to%20recruit%20Hank%20Greenspun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20Schwimmer%20showed%20up%20at%20his%20door%2C%20Greenspun%20was%20already%20embroiled%20in%20an%20organization%20as%20shadowy%20as%20the%20Haganah.%20For%20several%20years%20he%20had%20served%20as%20the%20publicist%20for%20the%20city's%20most%20notorious%20mobster%2C%20Bugsy%20Siegel.%20A%20fiery%2038-year-old%20with%20a%20shock%20of%20dark%20hair%20and%20a%20Vegas%20tan%2C%20Greenspun%20shared%20roots%20that%20were%20remarkably%20similar%20to%20Schwimmer's%3A%20Both%20were%20raised%20by%20poor%20Jewish%20immigrants%20in%20Connecticut%2C%20shaped%20by%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20and%20decorated%20in%20World%20War%20II.%20After%20the%20war%2C%20Greenspun%20had%20put%20aside%20his%20law%20practice%20to%20pursue%20his%20passion%20for%20journalism%2C%20launching%20a%20weekly%20tabloid%20called%20The%20Vegas%20Life.%20His%20work%20had%20garnered%20the%20attention%20of%20Siegel%2C%20who%20hired%20him%20to%20promote%20the%20Flamingo%2C%20his%20new%20resort%20on%20the%20Strip.%20But%20now%20Siegel%20had%20been%20gunned%20down%20in%20what%20appeared%20to%20be%20a%20mob%20hit%2C%20and%20Greenspun%20was%20looking%20for%20a%20fresh%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221771%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Al%20Schwimmer%20and%20Hank%20Greenspun%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fb31b7895d82203032bb1d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221216%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20Schwimmer%20(left)%20recruited%20Hank%20Greenspun%20(right)%20as%20his%20weapons%20expert%2C%20Greenspun%20had%20been%20working%20for%20Bugsy%20Siegel%2C%20the%20notorious%20mobster.%3Cp%3EL%3A%20Courtesy%20of%20Boaz%20Dvir%3B%20R%3A%20Los%20Angeles%20Examiner%2FUSC%20Libraries%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20Schwimmer%20had%20in%20mind%20was%20every%20bit%20as%20illegal%20as%20Siegel's%20operation.%20He%20explained%20his%20mission%20to%20Greenspun%2C%20who%20had%20specialized%20in%20munitions%20during%20the%20war.%20%26quot%3BI%20came%20straight%20to%20the%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20recalled%20Schwimmer.%20%26quot%3BWe%20needed%20his%20expertise.%26quot%3B%20Working%20off%20a%20%26quot%3Bhot%20tip%26quot%3B%20about%20a%20salvage%20yard%20in%20Hawaii%20that%20was%20thought%20to%20be%20sitting%20on%20more%20than%20500%20acres%20of%20airplane%20parts%2C%20engines%2C%20and%20weaponry%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bthe%20kind%20of%20stuff%20we%20really%20need%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20Schwimmer%20asked%20Greenspun%20to%20enlist%20in%20the%20cause.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20you%20to%20go%20there%20and%20check%20it%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fwgbh%2Famericanexperience%2Ffeatures%2Flasvegas-greenspun%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreenspun%3C%2Fa%3E%20shared%20Schwimmer's%20support%20of%20the%20Jewish%20people.%20But%20he%20had%20family%20%E2%80%94%20a%20wife%20and%20two%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20to%20consider.%20He%20told%20Schwimmer%20he%20was%20supposed%20to%20meet%20his%20wife%20that%20night%20at%20the%20Flamingo%20and%20take%20her%20to%20the%20opening%20of%20a%20radio%20station.%20Schwimmer%20told%20him%20he%20would%20have%20to%20call%20her%20from%20the%20road.%20Counting%20on%20Greenspun%20volunteering%2C%20he%20had%20already%20booked%20his%20flight%20to%20Hawaii.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20Greenspun%20arrived%20in%20Oahu%2C%20where%20he%20met%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20salvage%20yard%2C%20Nathan%20Liff.%20The%20balding%20Jewish%20guy%20%26quot%3Blooked%20like%20Santa%20Claus%20in%20a%20brightly%20patterned%20aloha%20shirt%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Greenspun%20wrote%20in%20his%20memoir%2C%20%26quot%3BWhere%20I%20Stand.%26quot%3B%20Liff%2C%20who%20spoke%20Yiddish%2C%20had%20also%20lost%20family%20in%20the%20Holocaust.%20The%20year%20before%2C%20his%20salvage%20yard%20had%20won%20a%20government%20contract%20to%20junk%20tons%20of%20surplus%20war%20munitions.%20Greenspun%20was%20amazed%20to%20see%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%20of%20machine%20guns%2C%20ripped%20from%20the%20turrets%20of%20junked%20planes.%26quot%3B%20He%20walked%20over%20to%20the%20nearest%20pile%20for%20a%20closer%20look.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20thirty%20calibers%20and%20heavy%20fifties%2C%20water-%20and%20air-cooled%20jobs%20in%20profusion%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BI%20checked%20the%20action%20on%20the%20guns%20and%20found%20that%20they%20functioned%20almost%20as%20smoothly%20as%20new.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiff%2C%20like%20Greenspun%2C%20was%20galvanized%20by%20the%20Holocaust.%20%26quot%3BHe%20felt%20he%20had%20to%20do%20his%20part%20in%20creating%20a%20Jewish%20state%2C%20so%20this%20could%20never%20happen%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimmer%20recalled.%20Rather%20than%20melt%20down%20the%20surplus%20weapons%20for%20scrap%2C%20Liff%20told%20Greenspun%20to%20take%20as%20much%20as%20he%20wanted%20%E2%80%94%20free%20of%20charge.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20sell%20him%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20Liff%20later%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BI%20gave%20it%20to%20him%20as%20a%20present.%20I%20knew%20what%20they%20needed%20it%20for%2C%20and%20they%20had%20no%20money.%20Today%20it's%20new%2C%20tomorrow%20it's%20junk.%20I'm%20in%20the%20junk%20business.%20I%20told%20them%20to%20take%20it%20away%2C%20to%20take%20what%20they%20needed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222499%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Haganah%20soldiers%20training%20with%20mortars%20and%20machine%20guns%2C%20Tel%20Aviv%2C%20Israel%2C%20May%206%2C%201948.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fb48d94af076d3cf92344d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221827%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGreenspun%20managed%20to%20smuggle%2058%20crates%20of%20weapons%20to%20Israel%2C%20where%20the%20Haganah%20was%20training%20soldiers%20in%201948.%20%3Cp%3EPhotoQuest%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20junkyard%2C%20Greenspun%20used%20a%20forklift%20to%20load%20airplane%20parts%20into%20crates.%20But%20he%20knew%20that%20the%20Jews%20in%20Palestine%20would%20need%20even%20more%20munitions%20to%20defend%20themselves.%20As%20he%20worked%2C%20he%20noticed%20that%20there%20was%20an%20even%20larger%20supply%20of%20surplus%20guns%20and%20parts%20right%20next%20door%2C%20at%20the%20US%20Naval%20Yard.%20Though%20it%20was%20heavily%20protected%2C%20Greenspun%20figured%20out%20that%20every%20two%20hours%2C%20there%20was%20an%20eight-minute%20gap%20between%20the%20guards%20who%20patrolled%20the%20perimeter%20%E2%80%94%20just%20enough%20time%20for%20him%20to%20drive%20in%20a%20forklift%20and%20steal%20as%20many%20weapons%20as%20he%20could%20get%20his%20hands%20on.%20Working%20under%20the%20cover%20of%20night%2C%20he%20made%20off%20with%2058%20crates%20of%20weapons%20and%20parts.%20The%20plan%20was%20to%20ship%20them%20on%20a%20freighter%20to%20Schwimmer%20Aviation%20in%20California%2C%20and%20then%20on%20to%20Palestine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20Burbank%2C%20Schwimmer%20and%20his%20smugglers%20were%20waiting.%20So%20was%20the%20FBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2029%2C%201947%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20voted%20to%20divide%20Palestine%20between%20the%20Jews%20living%20there%20and%20the%20Arabs%20whose%20homeland%20it%20had%20been%20for%20centuries.%20That%20same%20month%2C%20the%20United%20States%20imposed%20a%20total%20embargo%20on%20shipping%20arms%20to%20Palestine.%20Come%20the%20following%20May%2C%20when%20the%20new%20state%20of%20Israel%20would%20declare%20its%20independence%2C%20the%20UN%20would%20pull%20out%20of%20the%20region%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20full-fledged%20war%20was%20sure%20to%20ensue.%20Without%20an%20air%20force%2C%20Israel%20was%20almost%20certain%20to%20lose.%20And%20the%20only%20shot%20at%20getting%20one%20was%20from%20Schwimmer%20and%20his%20fellow%20smugglers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20as%20Schwimmer%20was%20working%20with%20his%20crew%20at%20Schwimmer%20Aviation%2C%20a%20clean-cut%20man%20in%20a%20dark%20suit%20approached%20him.%20Bernarr%20McFadden%20%26quot%3BPat%26quot%3B%20Ptacek%20was%20one%20of%20the%20FBI's%20most%20notorious%20agents.%20Earlier%20that%20year%2C%20his%20investigations%20had%20helped%20provoke%20the%20signing%20of%20an%20executive%20order%20designed%20to%20root%20out%20communists%20supposedly%20lurking%20by%20the%20hundreds%20in%20the%20corridors%20of%20Washington.%20Now%2C%20Ptacek%20informed%20Schwimmer%2C%20he%20had%20a%20new%20target%3A%20rooting%20out%20Americans%20who%20were%20breaking%20the%20arms%20embargo%20on%20Palestine.%20The%20Feds%20didn't%20have%20enough%20proof%20yet%20to%20bust%20Schwimmer%2C%20but%20Ptacek%20assured%20him%20it%20was%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwimmer%20didn't%20take%20any%20chances.%20Shortly%20after%20the%20crates%20of%20munitions%20arrived%20from%20Oahu%2C%20he%20and%20his%20team%20hid%20them%20in%20a%20warehouse%20in%20Burbank.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20agents%20from%20the%20Customs%20Service%20stormed%20the%20docks%20looking%20for%20the%20weapons%2C%20and%20confiscated%20every%20crate%20that%20hadn't%20been%20secreted%20away.%20The%20close%20call%20left%20some%20of%20the%20veterans%20feeling%20conflicted.%20%26quot%3BIt%20went%20against%20the%20grain%20to%20buck%20the%20same%20government%20we%20had%20fought%20to%20preserve%20only%20a%20few%20years%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20Hank%20Greenspun%20recalled.%20But%20their%20loyalties%20were%20now%20divided%20%E2%80%94%20between%20the%20country%20they%20called%20home%2C%20and%20the%20one%20they%20saw%20as%20a%20new%20homeland%20for%20their%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20help%20of%20the%20Haganah%2C%20Schwimmer%20and%20Greenspun%20engineered%20a%20plan%20to%20ship%20the%20stolen%20weapons%20to%20Acapulco%2C%20where%20underground%20contacts%20would%20arrange%20to%20smuggle%20them%20to%20Palestine.%20Volunteers%20at%20the%20warehouse%20in%20Burbank%20%E2%80%94%20film%20producers%2C%20businessmen%2C%20lawyers%2C%20dentists%20%E2%80%94%20worked%20in%20shifts%20for%20a%20week%2C%20oiling%20and%20packing%20the%20guns.%20Unaware%20of%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20crates%2C%20a%20wealthy%20volunteer%20offered%20to%20transport%20them%20to%20Mexico%20aboard%20his%2060-foot%20schooner%2C%20Idalia%2C%20for%20%243%2C000.%20But%20on%20the%20night%20the%20boat%20was%20loaded%2C%20when%20he%20realized%20what%20the%20crates%20contained%2C%20he%20raised%20his%20price%20to%20%2417%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreenspun%20refused%20to%20pay.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Idalia%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20going%20all%20the%20way%20to%20Acapulco%20and%20it's%20taking%20the%20guns%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20man.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20bitch%20all%20you%20want%2C%20but%20that's%20the%20way%20it%20has%20to%20be.%26quot%3B%20When%20the%20man%20asked%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20he%20refused%2C%20Greenspun%20pulled%20out%20his%20Mauser%20and%20pressed%20it%20to%20the%20man's%20temple.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20blow%20your%20brains%20out%20and%20heave%20you%20over%20the%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20The%20ship%20left%20California%20with%20the%20crates%20and%20Greenspun%20aboard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBehind%20the%20scenes%2C%20the%20Haganah%20had%20been%20negotiating%20with%20the%20Mexican%20government%20to%20not%20only%20ship%20the%20arms%20to%20Palestine%2C%20but%20also%20to%20procure%20more%20weapons.%20Greenspun%2C%20armed%20with%20millions%20of%20dollars%20from%20the%20Haganah%2C%20served%20as%20chief%20purchasing%20agent.%20Operating%20out%20of%20a%20hotel%20in%20Mexico%20City%2C%20he%20spent%20months%20crisscrossing%20Central%20and%20South%20America%2C%20meeting%20with%20arms%20dealers%20and%20dictators%2C%20including%20Rafael%20Trujillo%20of%20the%20Dominican%20Republic.%20%26quot%3BWe%20inspected%20mountains%20of%20guns%20and%20acres%20of%20ammunition%2C%26quot%3B%20Greenspun%20recalled%2C%20%26quot%3Bprying%20up%20tarpaulins%2C%20spot-checking%20the%20firing%20mechanisms%20of%20rifles%20and%20machine%20guns%2C%20and%20testing%20the%20recoil%20tubes%20of%20cannons.%26quot%3B%20Five%20percent%20of%20every%20purchase%20was%20paid%20to%20the%20Mexican%20authorities%2C%20in%20cash.%20When%20the%20Mexican%20government%20grew%20nervous%20about%20violating%20the%20US%20embargo%20on%20Palestine%2C%20Greenspun%20created%20a%20cover%3A%20He%20pretended%20they%20were%20shipping%20the%20arms%20to%20China.%20To%20forge%20the%20necessary%20documentation%2C%20he%20stole%20stationery%20from%20the%20Chinese%20Embassy%20in%20Mexico%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmuggling%20so%20many%20arms%20also%20required%20smuggling%20the%20huge%20sums%20of%20money%20needed%20to%20pay%20for%20them%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0as%20well%20as%20bribes.%20%26quot%3BMy%20dad%20said%20they%20were%20always%20paying%20people%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20Danny%20recalls.%20One%20day%20at%20the%20Hotel%20Fourteen%2C%20Schwimmer%20told%20me%2C%20the%20group%20needed%20to%20get%20a%20large%20sum%20to%20the%20port%20of%20New%20York%2C%20to%20pay%20the%20captain%20of%20a%20ship%20bound%20with%20their%20weapons%20to%20Israel.%20But%20the%20Haganah's%20representative%20in%20America%2C%20Teddy%20Kollek%2C%20knew%20FBI%20agents%20were%20lurking%20outside%20the%20hotel.%20So%20he%20pulled%20aside%20a%20young%20singer%20who%20was%20coming%20out%20of%20the%20Copacabana%3A%20Frank%20Sinatra.%20An%20early%20supporter%20of%20Israel%2C%20Sinatra%20listened%20to%20Kollek's%20predicament%20and%20agreed%20to%20deliver%20the%20money%20himself.%20%26quot%3BDespite%20Sinatra's%20reputation%20as%20connected%20with%20the%20Italian%20mafia%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimmer%20later%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20penny%20was%20missing%20from%20the%20bag.%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tabletmag.com%2Fsections%2Fhistory%2Farticles%2Fteddy-kollek-yitzhak-ben-aharon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKollek%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Sinatra%20would%20go%20on%20to%20become%20lifelong%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20Schwimmer%20himself%20served%20as%20a%20mule%2C%20heading%20to%20Mexico%20with%20%24250%2C000%20in%20a%20briefcase%20and%20a%20pistol%20tucked%20into%20his%20belt.%20The%20limping%20kid%20who%20had%20fantasized%20about%20being%20Dick%20Tracy%20was%20suddenly%20heading%20across%20the%20border%20with%20a%20fake%20passport%20and%20an%20alias%2C%20Erwin%20Johnson.%20But%20when%20Schwimmer%20arrived%2C%20he%20was%20pulled%20over%20by%20a%20Mexican%20police%20officer%2C%20who%20discovered%20his%20pistol.%20%26quot%3BA%20gringo%20isn't%20supposed%20to%20carry%20a%20gun%20in%20Mexico%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20cop%20told%20him.%20Schwimmer%20was%20terrified.%20%26quot%3BI%20knew%20that%20if%20I%20ever%20entered%20the%20police%20station%2C%20I%20would%20never%20walk%20out%20of%20it%20alive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BI%20wondered%20how%20they%20would%20dispose%20of%20my%20body.%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20the%20cop%20asked%20him%20for%20a%20bribe%20of%20%2420.%20Considering%20the%20fortune%20in%20Schwimmer's%20briefcase%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20a%20bargain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20one%20thing%20to%20ship%20crates%20of%20weapons%20to%20Palestine%20%E2%80%94%20all%20it%20took%20was%20forged%20documents%20and%20plenty%20of%20money.%20But%20smuggling%20planes%20required%20a%20more%20elaborate%20ruse.%20And%20it%20started%20in%20a%20place%20few%20would%20suspect%3A%20Panama.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20the%20Panamanian%20government%20was%20planning%20to%20launch%20a%20national%20airline%20for%20civilian%20flights.%20There%20was%20only%20one%20snag%3A%20The%20country%20didn't%20have%20any%20planes.%20Schwimmer%20realized%20if%20he%20could%20lease%20his%20surplus%20planes%20to%20Panama%2C%20he%20could%20fly%20them%20there%20legally%20and%20then%20take%20them%20on%20to%20Palestine.%20Under%20the%20guise%20of%20a%20fake%20company%2C%20Service%20Airways%2C%20he%20rented%20nearly%20a%20dozen%20planes%20to%20Panama%20to%20launch%20its%20national%20airline%2C%20known%20as%20LAPSA.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20afraid%20that%20at%20any%20given%20moment%20the%20Panamanian%20government%20will%20catch%20on%2C%20and%20we'll%20all%20find%20ourselves%20in%20a%20jail%20cell%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221990%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20group%20of%20men%20in%20front%20of%20a%20plane%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fb35fd2417f97b87cdd759%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMembers%20of%20the%20operation%20in%20Corsica%2C%20en%20route%20with%20one%20of%20the%20planes%20they%20smuggled%20to%20Israel.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Boaz%20Dvir%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20heading%20to%20Panama%2C%20Schwimmer%20met%20with%20a%20Haganah%20agent%20in%20New%20York%20who%20brought%20him%20a%20roll%20of%20microfilm%2C%20hidden%20in%20his%20underwear.%20It%20contained%20maps%20of%20makeshift%20landing%20strips%20hidden%20in%20some%20orange%20groves%20near%20Tel%20Aviv%2C%20where%20the%20planes%20could%20land%2C%20along%20with%20secret%20codes%20to%20use%20en%20route.%20Israel%20was%20%26quot%3BOklahoma%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20United%20States%20was%20%26quot%3BDetroit%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20Panama%20was%20%26quot%3BLatin%20Detroit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20at%203%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20as%20the%20planes%20were%20preparing%20to%20depart%2C%20Schwimmer%20got%20a%20call.%20A%20federal%20official%20informed%20him%20that%20he%20had%20failed%20to%20receive%20approval%20from%20the%20State%20Department%2C%20which%20was%20required%20for%20all%20international%20flights.%20%26quot%3BThey%20forbade%20us%20to%20fly%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimmer%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BI%20ignored%20the%20order.%20We%20had%20come%20too%20far%20to%20stop%2C%20an%20hour%20before%20our%20scheduled%20takeoff.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20planes%20from%20Burbank%20stopped%20in%20Mexico%20City%20to%20refuel%20before%20continuing%20on%20to%20Panama.%20They%20were%20packed%20with%20weapons%20%E2%80%94%20more%20cargo%2C%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20than%20they%20were%20designed%20to%20handle.%20As%20one%20of%20the%20planes%20ascended%20to%2017%2C000%20feet%2C%20the%20pilot%2C%20Bill%20Gerson%2C%20lost%20control.%20The%20plane%20plunged%20to%20the%20runway%20below%2C%20killing%20Gerson%20and%20his%20mechanic%2C%20Bud%20King.%20They%20were%20both%20veterans%20of%20World%20War%20II%20who%20believed%20in%20Schwimmer's%20cause%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20were%20the%20first%20to%20die%20for%20it.%20They%20wouldn't%20be%20the%20last.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20half-century%20later%2C%20Schwimmer%20was%20still%20haunted%20by%20the%20crash.%20He%20couldn't%20forget%20how%2C%20when%20he%20met%20with%20Gerson's%20wife%2C%20she%20had%20slapped%20him%20and%20called%20him%20a%20murderer.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20heartbroken%2C%26quot%3B%20Rina%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BHe%20felt%20for%20many%20years%20that%20it%20was%20his%20fault.%20He%20overloaded%20the%20airplanes%2C%20because%20Ben-Gurion%20was%20screaming%2C%20'We%20don't%20have%20bullets%20for%20our%20guns!%20We%20need%20ammunition%20immediately!'%26quot%3B%20Schwimmer%20took%20responsibility%20for%20overloading%20the%20plane.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20overweight%2C%20and%20I%20am%20to%20blame%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Greenspun%20and%20his%20team.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we%20have%20to%20do%20this.%20This%20is%20necessary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20showing%20the%20smugglers%20route%20from%20Burbank%20to%20Tel%20Aviv%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fb366d895d82203032bdf4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22983%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20smugglers%20took%20a%20long%20and%20circuitous%20route%20to%20smuggle%20the%20planes%20from%20California%20to%20Israel.%3Cp%3EJoel%20Kimmel%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20May%206%2C%201948%2C%20just%20eight%20days%20before%20Israel%20declared%20independence%2C%20Panamanian%20officials%2C%20military%20leaders%2C%20and%20celebrities%20gathered%20at%20the%20airport%20to%20witness%20the%20arrival%20of%20planes%20the%20press%20had%20dubbed%20%26quot%3Bthe%20pride%20of%20Panama.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BEverybody%20from%20the%20Panamanian%20government%20with%20wives%20and%20children%20came%20to%20see%20this%20miracle%2C%26quot%3B%20Rina%20recalled.%20Schwimmer's%20planes%2C%20now%20bearing%20the%20LAPSA%20logo%20and%20Panamanian%20registration%20numbers%2C%20eased%20down%20the%20tarmac%20as%20a%20brass%20band%20played.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20new%20era%20for%20the%20people%20of%20Panama%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20pilot%20Sam%20Lewis%20told%20the%20crowd.%20A%20group%20of%20tourists%20and%20officials%2C%20armed%20with%20several%20crates%20of%20Pepsi%2C%20were%20taken%20on%20a%20demonstration%20flight.%20Then%20Lewis%20and%20the%20other%20pilots%20took%20off%2C%20flying%20away%20in%20a%20long%20procession%20until%20they%20disappeared%20into%20the%20horizon.%20Unbeknownst%20to%20Panama%2C%20its%20new%20national%20airline%20was%20on%20its%20way%20to%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20took%20off%20during%20the%20parade%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Danny%20Schwimmer%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20they%20never%20came%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20war%20in%20Israel%20fast%20approaching%2C%20the%20smuggled%20planes%20made%20their%20way%20toward%20Tel%20Aviv%3Cem%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3ESchwimmer%20and%20his%20team%20had%20arranged%20for%20refueling%20stops%20along%20the%20way.%20From%20Panama%2C%20the%20planes%20flew%20to%20Suriname%2C%20then%20on%20through%20Brazil%20and%20Senegal%2C%20before%20landing%20in%20Casablanca.%20There%2C%20the%20pilots%20encountered%20a%20crowd%20of%20protesters%2C%20raging%20over%20Israel's%20coming%20independence%20and%20chanting%20%26quot%3BKill%20the%20Jews!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221771%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Meyer%20Lansky%20and%20Bugsy%20Siegel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fb36c54af076d3cf9229c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221216%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMeyer%20Lansky%20(left)%2C%20who%20had%20been%20partners%20with%20Bugsy%20Siegel%20(right)%2C%20helped%20the%20smugglers%20refuel%20in%20Sicily.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20stop%20was%20Catania%2C%20Sicily%2C%20where%20the%20Mafia%20had%20arranged%20for%20refueling%20through%20a%20man%20sympathetic%20to%20the%20cause%3A%20the%20gangster%20Meyer%20Lansky.%20Lansky%2C%20who%20had%20been%20partners%20with%20Greenspun's%20former%20boss%2C%20Bugsy%20Siegel%2C%20was%20a%20staunch%20Zionist%20who%20had%20been%20funneling%20money%20and%20arms%20to%20the%20Haganah.%20But%20when%20members%20of%20Schwimmer's%20team%20landed%20in%20Sicily%2C%20the%20local%20mobsters%20hadn't%20gotten%20the%20word%20and%20angrily%20confronted%20the%20Americans.%20The%20shaken%20pilots%2C%20unable%20to%20converse%20in%20Italian%2C%20uttered%20two%20words%3A%20%26quot%3BMeyer%20Lansky.%26quot%3B%20They%20spent%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20time%20in%20Sicily%20enjoying%20the%20local%20cuisine%2C%20and%20departed%20with%20a%20gift%3A%20a%20crateful%20of%20Tommy%20guns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20planes%20weren't%20the%20only%20ones%20Schwimmer%20and%20his%20team%20smuggled%20into%20Israel.%20Ben-Gurion%2C%20as%20Schwimmer%20later%20recalled%2C%20had%20received%20a%20coded%20message%20from%20Europe.%20Czechoslovakia%20was%20also%20willing%20to%20sell%20arms%20to%20Israel%2C%20both%20for%20the%20money%20and%20as%20a%20statement%20of%20support.%20And%20the%20Czechs%20had%20just%20the%20thing%20to%20help%20the%20Jews%20fight%20for%20independence%3A%20surplus%20Nazi%20warplanes.%20A%20Czech%20Holocaust%20survivor%20provided%20Schwimmer's%20team%20with%2025%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.topwar.ru%2F85280-messershmitty-na-vooruzhenii-armii-oborony-izrailya.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMesserschmitts%3C%2Fa%3E%20left%20over%20from%20the%20war.%20There%20was%20just%20one%20problem%3A%20the%20giant%20swastikas%20painted%20on%20the%20tails%20of%20some%20of%20the%20planes.%20So%20the%20Americans%20scrounged%20up%20some%20buckets%20of%20white%20paint.%20%26quot%3BThe%20swastika%20was%20removed%2C%20and%20replaced%20with%20the%20Star%20of%20David%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwimmer%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BThe%20irony%20of%20it%20%E2%80%94%20German%20Messerschmitts%2C%20produced%20in%20Czechoslovakia%2C%20flown%20by%20American%20Jewish%20pilots%20fighting%20for%20the%20creation%20and%20protection%20of%20the%20Jewish%20state.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221771%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20image%20of%20a%20plane%20next%20to%20an%20image%20of%20a%20crashed%20plane%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fb3ba4895d82203032c0ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20German%20Messerschmitt%20transformed%20into%20an%20Israeli%20Avia%20S-199%20(left).%20The%20tail%20of%20a%20Czech%20cargo%20plane%20(right)%20that%20crashed%20en%20route%20to%20Israel.%20%3Cp%3EL%3A%20Public%20Domain%3B%20R%3A%20Courtesy%20of%20Boaz%20Dvir%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJoined%20by%20the%20planes%20from%20Burbank%2C%20the%20Messerschmitt%20pilots%20headed%20for%20a%20secret%20airfield%20hidden%20in%20the%20orange%20groves%20north%20of%20Tel%20Aviv%2C%20with%20a%20landing%20strip%20%26quot%3Blit%20by%20tin%20cans%20filled%20with%20sand%20and%20burning%20oil%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Schwimmer%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20else%20was%20just%20as%20primitive%2C%20including%20the%20single%20shabby%20hangar.%26quot%3B%20The%20conditions%20proved%20deadly%3A%20One%20of%20the%20Czech%20planes%20crash-landed%2C%20killing%20the%20navigator.%20But%20one%20by%20one%2C%20the%20other%20planes%20landed%20safely.%20Schwimmer%20had%20pulled%20off%20a%20seemingly%20impossible%20heist%3A%20stealing%20planes%20and%20arms%20that%20had%20belonged%20to%20both%20the%20Nazis%20and%20the%20Americans%2C%20and%20delivering%20them%20to%20Israel.%20With%20a%20single%20stroke%2C%20he%20had%20given%20the%20Jewish%20state%20its%20very%20own%20air%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsrael%20quickly%20deployed%20the%20planes%20in%20battle.%20The%20first%20air%20attack%20succeeded%20in%20halting%20the%20Egyptian%20advance%20on%20Tel%20Aviv.%20During%20the%20second%20attack%2C%20the%20fighter%20pilot%20Milt%20Rubenfeld%20was%20met%20with%20enemy%20gunfire%20over%20Egypt%2C%20and%20had%20to%20parachute%20out%20of%20his%20plane%20near%20a%20remote%20village.%20Because%20the%20Jewish%20locals%20didn't%20know%20their%20fledgling%20country%20had%20an%20air%20force%2C%20they%20readied%20to%20shoot%20Rubenfeld%2C%20assuming%20him%20to%20be%20an%20enemy%20pilot.%20He%20saved%20himself%20by%20shouting%20the%20only%20words%20of%20Hebrew%20he%20knew.%20%26quot%3BGefilte%20fish!%26quot%3B%20he%20yelled.%20%26quot%3BShabbos!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20planes%20followed%2C%20including%20B-17%20bombers%20that%20Schwimmer%20had%20acquired%20back%20in%20the%20States.%20Schwimmer%20was%20aboard%20one%20of%20the%20bombers%2C%20en%20route%20to%20Tel%20Aviv%2C%20when%20he%20received%20an%20urgent%20message%20from%20the%20Israeli%20military%20command.%20The%20Egyptians%20were%20advancing%2C%20and%20Israeli%20troops%20desperately%20needed%20air%20support.%20Schwimmer%20would%20have%20to%20drop%20the%20first%20bombs%20himself%2C%20as%20his%20plane%20flew%20over%20Cairo.%20The%20only%20way%20to%20do%20that%20was%20to%20manually%20open%20the%20hatch%20and%20roll%20out%20the%20bombs%20by%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFifty%20years%20later%2C%20at%20a%20Thanksgiving%20dinner%20in%20Connecticut%2C%20Schwimmer%20told%20me%20he%20recalled%20the%20plane%20flying%20so%20low%20that%20he%20could%20see%20an%20enemy%20soldier%20sitting%20in%20an%20outhouse.%20When%20I%20asked%20him%20how%20he%20felt%20at%20that%20moment%2C%20he%20paused.%20There%20wasn't%20time%20for%20feelings%2C%20he%20explained.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20would%20have%20killed%20us%20too%2C%20if%20they%20could.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2010%2C%201949%2C%20Israel%20won%20the%20war.%20Schwimmer's%20aid%20proved%20to%20be%20pivotal%20to%20the%20victory.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20Al's%20operation%2C%20Israel%20would%20have%20never%20survived%20its%20first%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Boaz%20Dvir%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Pennsylvania%20State%20University%20who's%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BSaving%20Israel%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20account%20of%20Schwimmer's%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20end%20of%20the%20war%20didn't%20end%20Schwimmer's%20battles.%20That%20October%2C%20Schwimmer%20and%20others%20in%20his%20group%2C%20including%20Hank%20Greenspun%2C%20were%20put%20on%20trial%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20for%20violating%20the%20Neutrality%20Act.%20They%20faced%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20fines%20and%20years%20in%20federal%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBen-Gurion%20ensured%20the%20men%20had%20the%20best%20lawyers%20to%20defend%20them.%20Schwimmer%20pleaded%20not%20guilty.%20His%20defense%20was%20what%20he%20saw%20as%20the%20justness%20of%20his%20cause.%20%26quot%3BWe%20did%20not%20deny%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20smuggled%20planes%20and%20military%20equipment%2C%20as%20charged%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20insisted.%20%26quot%3BWe%20did%20nothing%20to%20endanger%20American%20security.%20All%20we%20did%20was%20protect%20a%20friendly%20nation%20from%20hostile%20surrounding%20armies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225053%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Palmach%20armoured%20unit%20fighting%20with%20the%20Israel%20Defence%20Forces%20during%20the%201948%20War%20of%20Independence%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fb3c534af076d3cf922d96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223358%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Haganah%20elite%20fighting%20unit%20in%201948.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20Al's%20operation%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20historian%2C%20%26quot%3BIsrael%20would%20have%20never%20survived%20its%20first%20war.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EUniversal%20History%20Archive%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20attorney%20for%20the%20arms%20smugglers%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20men%20on%20trial%20were%20American%20heroes%20who%20had%20served%20their%20country%20during%20World%20War%20II.%20Some%2C%20like%20Schwimmer%2C%20had%20lost%20family%20in%20the%20Holocaust.%20When%20a%20prosecutor%20suggested%20that%20one%20of%20the%20non-Jews%20on%20trial%2C%20Charlie%20Winters%2C%20had%20sold%20the%20group%20B-17s%20just%20to%20make%20a%20quick%20buck%2C%20Winters%20said%20his%20support%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20money.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20Irish%2C%20and%20I%20hate%20the%20British%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20what%20he%20saw%20as%20England's%20abandonment%20of%20Israel.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20aware%20of%20where%20my%20B-17%20were%20destined%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWinters%20was%20found%20guilty%20and%20received%2018%20months%20in%20prison.%20Schwimmer%20and%20Greenspun%2C%20along%20with%20others%20involved%20in%20the%20operation%2C%20were%20convicted%20and%20fined%20%2410%2C000%2C%20but%20weren't%20sentenced%20to%20prison.%20Schwimmer%20felt%20%26quot%3Bappalled%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20verdict.%20%26quot%3BJustice%20and%20the%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Baren't%20always%20on%20the%20same%20page.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20law%2C%20and%20of%20many%20who%20opposed%20the%20creation%20of%20Israel%2C%20Schwimmer%20and%20his%20crew%20were%20nothing%20but%20criminals%20%E2%80%94%20convicted%20arms%20smugglers%20who%20stole%20government%20property%2C%20violated%20an%20American%20embargo%2C%20and%20illegally%20took%20sides%20in%20a%20foreign%20conflict.%20But%20history%20has%20a%20way%20of%20switching%20sides.%20As%20the%20years%20passed%20and%20Israel%20became%20one%20of%20America's%20closest%20allies%2C%20what%20was%20once%20viewed%20as%20treasonous%20came%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20an%20act%20of%20heroism.%20Greenspun%2C%20who%20later%20took%20on%20Joseph%20McCarthy%20as%20publisher%20of%20the%20Las%20Vegas%20Sun%2C%20was%20pardoned%20by%20President%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20in%201961.%20Despite%20his%20bravado%2C%20it%20meant%20a%20lot%20to%20him%20to%20be%20restored%20to%20his%20full%20rights%20as%20an%20American%20citizen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20dad%20was%20a%20World%20War%20II%20hero%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flasvegassun.com%2Fnews%2Fopinion%2Fcolumnists%2Fbrian-greenspun%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrian%20Greenspun%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20succeeded%20his%20father%20as%20publisher%20of%20the%20Sun%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20was%20kind%20of%20incongruous%20that%20he%20would%20do%20all%20this%20for%20his%20country%2C%20and%20yet%20he%20couldn't%20vote%20in%20his%20country.%20I'm%20sure%20it%20bothered%20him%20inside.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20conviction%2C%20Schwimmer%20was%20invited%20by%20Ben-Gurion%20to%20move%20to%20Israel%20and%20create%20the%20country's%20aerospace%20industry.%20He%20founded%20Israel%20Aerospace%20Industries%2C%20which%20manufactured%20aircraft%20for%20military%20and%20civilian%20use%2C%20and%20served%20as%20its%20first%20president.%20Today%20IAI%20is%20a%20state-owned%20company%20with%2014%2C000%20employees.%20The%20battered%20old%20planes%20Schwimmer%20provided%20to%20help%20Israel%20secure%20its%20independence%20have%20been%20replaced%20by%20fighter%20jets%2C%20missiles%2C%20and%20drones%20built%20by%20the%20company%20he%20founded.%20Today%20they're%20providing%20Israel%20with%20air%20superiority%20in%20a%20different%20war%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0this%20time%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223733%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Golda%20Meir%20and%20Al%20Schwimmer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fb3ce9895d82203032c1c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222335%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESchwimmer%20with%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Golda%20Meir.%20Today%20the%20aerospace%20company%20he%20founded%20has%2014%2C000%20employees.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Danny%20Schwimmer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20Schwimmer%20also%20remained%20active%20as%20an%20arms%20smuggler%2C%20helping%20to%20move%20American%20weapons%20during%20the%20Iran-Contra%20affair.%20Yet%20he%20refrained%20from%20seeking%20a%20pardon%20from%20the%20United%20States%2C%20where%20he%20continued%20to%20be%20deprived%20of%20his%20voting%20rights.%20As%20he%20told%20me%20many%20times%2C%20he%20felt%20he%20had%20done%20nothing%20that%20required%20pardoning.%20%26quot