er-chaos-at-2022-champions-league-final-in-paris-13100320%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fliverpool-fans-compensated-over-chaos-at-2022-champions-league-final-in-paris-13100320%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20Rajasthan%2C%20BJP%20and%20Congress%20Rely%20on%20Turncoats%20to%20Get%20Lok%20Sabha%20Election%20Arithmetic%20Right%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F23124305%2FScreenshot-2024-03-23-at-12.41.0.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJaipur%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20dramatic%20scene%20awaited%20the%20journalists%20present%20at%20the%20Rajasthan%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20headquarters%20in%20Jaipur%2C%20as%20two-time%20former%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20MLA%20Prahlad%20Gunjal%20emphatically%20proclaimed%20his%20seniority%20in%20the%20saffron%20party%2C%20which%20he%20quit%20before%20joining%20the%20Congress%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20had%20become%20the%20MLA%2C%20the%20Rajasthan%20chief%20minister%20was%20a%20sarpanch%2C%20while%20the%20incumbent%20BJP%20state%20president%20used%20to%20be%20a%20panchayat%20samiti%20member%2C%E2%80%9D%20Gunjal%20said%2C%20before%20vowing%20to%20work%20hard%20to%20strengthen%20the%20Congress%20%E2%80%94%20a%20party%20he%20till%20now%20had%20opposed%20bitterly%20in%20his%20four-decade-old%20political%20career%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20Hadoti%20region%20of%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGunjal%2C%20a%20loyalist%20of%20senior%20BJP%20leader%20and%20former%20chief%20minister%20Vasundhara%20Raje%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20declared%20as%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20for%20the%20Kota%20parliamentary%20seat%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20held%20by%20Lok%20Sabha%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla.%20After%20joining%20the%20Congress%2C%20Gunjal%20launched%20a%20scathing%20attack%20on%20the%20BJP%2C%20alleging%20that%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20common%20worker%20is%20being%20suppressed%20in%20his%20former%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGunjal%20was%20earlier%20fielded%20by%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20Assembly%20elections%20last%20year%20from%20the%20Kota%20North%20seat%20but%20lost%20to%20senior%20Congress%20leader%20Shanti%20Dhariwal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20Rajasthan%20Congress%20president%20Govind%20Singh%20Dotasra%20maintained%20that%20the%20decision%20to%20induct%20Gunjal%20was%20unanimously%20supported%20by%20all%20Congress%20leaders%2C%20Dhariwal%2C%20who%20shares%20a%20bitter%20relationship%20with%20Gunjal%2C%20was%20conspicuously%20missing%20from%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20induction%20ceremony%20at%20the%20Congress%20office%20in%20Jaipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defection%20of%20Gunjal%20just%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20shows%20the%20larger%20trend%20in%20both%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20and%20opposition%20Congress%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20wherein%20both%20the%20parties%20are%20relying%20on%20turncoats%20from%20other%20political%20parties%20to%20get%20the%20electoral%20arithmetic%20right%20in%20the%20state%20with%2025%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETribal%20politician%20quitting%20Congress%2C%20Jat%20politician%20leaving%20BJP%20over%20feud%20with%20Rajput%20leader%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20February%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20made%20the%20first%20move%20by%20inducting%20Congress%20MLA%20and%20senior%20politician%20Mahendrajeet%20Singh%20Malviya%20into%20its%20ranks%20and%20declaring%20him%20as%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20from%20the%20tribal%20dominated%20Banswara%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%2C%20where%20apart%20from%20the%20Congress%2C%20the%20Bharat%20Adivasi%20Party%20(BAP)%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20potent%20political%20force%20in%20recent%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20was%20quick%20to%20hit%20back%2C%20as%20Rahul%20Kaswan%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20incumbent%20MP%20from%20Churu%20joined%20the%20grand%20old%20party%20earlier%20this%20month.%20Subsequently%20he%20has%20been%20fielded%20by%20the%20Congress%20from%20the%20Churu%20seat%2C%20which%20Kaswan%20has%20won%20twice%20since%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahul%20Kaswan%E2%80%99s%20family%20%E2%80%94%20his%20father%20Ram%20Singh%20Kaswan%20is%20also%20a%20former%20MP%20from%20Churu%20%E2%80%94%20shifted%20to%20the%20Congress%20fold%20after%20the%20BJP%20denied%20a%20ticket%20to%20him%20and%20instead%20fielded%20Paralympian%20Devendra%20Jhajharia%20from%20the%20seat%2C%20making%20the%20contest%20for%20Churu%20one%20of%20the%20most%20interesting%20electoral%20battles%20in%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20denial%20of%20ticket%20to%20Kaswan%20by%20the%20BJP%20is%20a%20result%20of%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20feud%20with%20senior%20BJP%20leader%20Rajendra%20Rathore%2C%20a%20former%20seven-time%20MLA%20who%20was%20also%20the%20Rajasthan%20leader%20of%20opposition%20before%20the%20assembly%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERathore%2C%20a%20Rajput%2C%20along%20with%20the%20Kaswan%20family%2C%20which%20is%20from%20the%20Jat%20community%2C%20have%20decided%20the%20course%20of%20Churu%E2%80%99s%20politics%20in%20the%20last%20three%20decades%2C%20also%20strengthening%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20district.%20While%20Rathore%20was%20elected%20an%20MLA%20from%20seats%20in%20Churu%20district%20consecutively%20for%20seven%20times%20between%201990%20and%202023%2C%20the%20Churu%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%20has%20been%20held%20by%20a%20Kaswan%20family%20member%20since%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20camaraderie%20between%20Rathore%20and%20the%20Kaswan%20clan%20suffered%20after%20Rathore%E2%80%99s%20defeat%20in%20the%202023%20assembly%20elections%20from%20the%20Taranagar%20Assembly%20constituency%2C%20where%20Narendra%20Budania%2C%20a%20senior%20Congress%20MLA%20emerged%20victorious.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERathore%E2%80%99s%20supporters%20alleged%20that%20the%20Kaswan%20family%20was%20responsible%20for%20Rathore%E2%80%99s%20defeat%20by%20helping%20Congress%20candidate%20Budania%20and%20backstabbing%20Rathore%20in%20the%20electoral%20arena.%20Rathore%20himself%20termed%20those%20who%20%E2%80%98betrayed%E2%80%99%20him%20as%20%E2%80%98Jaichand%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20sitting%20MP%20Kaswan%20was%20denied%20a%20ticket%20by%20the%20BJP%2C%20it%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20counter%20attack%20by%20Rathore%2C%20who%20holds%20considerable%20influence%20in%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20Kaswan%20joined%20Congress%2C%20the%20electoral%20battle%20in%20Churu%20has%20become%20a%20Jat%20vs%20Rajput%20fight%2C%20with%20Kaswan%20against%20Jhajharia%2C%20who%20despite%20being%20a%20Jat%2C%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20proxy%20candidate%20for%20Rathore%2C%20a%20Rajput.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBehind%20defections%3A%20Focus%20on%20OBC%20votes%2C%20shrinking%20space%20for%20Raje%20loyalists%20in%20BJP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20BJP%20inducted%20several%20OBC%20Congress%20leaders%20including%20former%20MLAs%20Richpal%20Mirdha%2C%20his%20son%20Vijaypal%20Mirdha%20and%20former%20ministers%20Lalchand%20Kataria%20and%20Rajendra%20Singh%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Richpal%20Mirdha%20and%20his%20son%20VIjaypal%20Mirdha%20belong%20from%20the%20Mirdha%20clan%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20most%20influential%20Jat%20political%20families%20in%20Rajasthan%20%E2%80%94%20Kataria%20and%20Yadav%20were%20close%20aides%20of%20former%20chief%20minister%20Ashok%20Gehlot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Kataria%20and%20Yadav%20were%20ministers%20in%20the%20previous%20Ashok%20Gehlot%20government.%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20premises%20were%20also%20raided%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20in%20connection%20with%20an%20alleged%20mid%20day%20meal%20scam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhow-an-adivasi-party-is-changing-political-equations-in-southern-rajasthans-tribal-districts%5C%22%3EHow%20an%20Adivasi%20Party%20is%20Changing%20Political%20Equations%20in%20Southern%20Rajasthan%E2%80%99s%20Tribal%20Districts%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defections%20reflect%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20focus%20on%20the%20Jat%20and%20OBC%20votes%20in%20the%20state%2C%20where%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20has%20been%20winning%20all%2025%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20since%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJat%20leaders%20such%20as%20Mirdha%20and%20Kataria%20wield%20significant%20influence%20in%20districts%20such%20as%20Nagaur%20and%20Jaipur%20rural%20from%20where%20they%20have%20been%20elected%20as%20legislators%20and%20parliamentarians%2C%20while%20Yadav%20was%20among%20the%20most%20well%20known%20leaders%20of%20the%20Congress%20from%20the%20Yadav%20community%2C%20who%20are%20traditional%20voters%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20inducting%20strong%20OBC%20and%20Jats%20leaders%2C%20the%20BJP%20hopes%20to%20strengthen%20its%20grip%20in%20districts%20such%20as%20Nagaur%2C%20where%20the%20Jat%20votes%20decides%20the%20winner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20by%20fielding%20BJP%20turncoat%20Kaswan%2C%20the%20Congress%20hopes%20to%20give%20a%20tough%20fight%20to%20the%20BJP%20in%20Churu%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Shekhawati%20region.%20Even%20though%20the%20Congress%20lost%20the%202023%20assembly%20elections%2C%20it%20had%20outperformed%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20Shekhawati%20belt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEyeing%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20in%20Western%20Rajasthan%2C%20the%20Congress%20has%20declared%20Umeda%20Ram%20Beniwal%20a%20turncoat%20from%20the%20Hanuman%20Beniwal-led%20Rashtriya%20Loktantrik%20Party%20(RLP)%20as%20its%20candidate%20from%20the%20Jat%20dominated%20Barmer%20parliamentary%20seat.%20Beniwal%20will%20take%20on%20Union%20Minister%20Kailash%20Choudhary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20the%20Rajasthan%20BJP%20has%20seen%20a%20leadership%20change%20is%20also%20instrumental%20behind%20its%20established%20leaders%20joining%20the%20Congress.%20Seasoned%20BJP%20politicians%20such%20as%20%C2%A0Kaswan%20and%20Gunjal%20were%20counted%20among%20staunch%20supporters%20of%20former%20chief%20minister%20Raje%2C%20who%20was%20not%20given%20a%20third%20term%20by%20the%20saffron%20party%20leadership%20after%20they%20came%20to%20power%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20BJP%20central%20leadership%20now%20calling%20the%20shots%20in%20Rajasthan%20where%20Bhajan%20Lal%20Sharma%2C%20a%20first-time%20MLA%2C%20was%20made%20the%20chief%20minister%20instead%20of%20Raje%2C%20the%20former%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20supporters%20now%20find%20themselves%20staring%20at%20an%20uncertain%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711179013000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F23124305%2FScreenshot-2024-03-23-at-12.41.0.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fin-rajasthan-bjp-and-congress-rely-on-turncoats-to-get-lok-sabha-election-arithmetic-right%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20the%20BJP%20central%20leadership%20now%20calling%20the%20shots%20in%20Rajasthan%20where%20Bhajan%20Lal%20Sharma%2C%20a%20first-time%20MLA%2C%20was%20made%20the%20chief%20minister%20instead%20of%20Raje%2C%20the%20former%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20supporters%20now%20find%20themselves%20staring%20at%20an%20uncertain%20future.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fin-rajasthan-bjp-and-congress-rely-on-turncoats-to-get-lok-sabha-election-arithmetic-right%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Only%20Eight%20of%2030%20Sensex%20Companies%20Disclosed%20Political%20Donations%20in%20Past%20Five%20Fiscals%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F14185439%2Fcoins-gebbaa9855_1280.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Only%20eight%20of%2030%20Sensex%20companies%20disclosed%20their%20electoral%20bond%20purchases%20or%20other%20financial%20contributions%20to%20political%20parties%20in%20their%20annual%20reports%20at%20least%20once%20in%20the%20past%20five%20financial%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fonly-8-sensex-firms-disclosed-making-political-contribution-in-last-5-years-124032201044_1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECollectively%2C%20these%20companies%20spent%20Rs%20628%20crore%20on%20political%20contributions%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20the%20business%20daily%20said%2C%20citing%20their%20annual%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20telecom%20major%20Bharti%20Airtel%20contributed%20the%20highest%20amount%20of%20Rs%20241%20crore%2C%20followed%20by%20Tata%20Steel%20(Rs%20175%20crore)%20and%20Larsen%20%26amp%3B%20Toubro%20(Rs%2085%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBharti%20Airtel%20emerged%20as%20the%20only%20Sensex%20company%20that%20consistently%20donated%20to%20political%20parties%20each%20year%2C%20in%20the%20past%20five%20financial%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20its%20annual%20reports%2C%20the%20company%20and%20its%20subsidiaries%20collectively%20donated%20Rs%20241%20crore%20to%20political%20parties%20between%20FY19%20and%20FY23%2C%20either%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20or%20contributions%20to%20electoral%20trusts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COther%20expenses%20include%20political%20contributions%20amounting%20to%20Rs%20300%20million%20(Rs%2030%20crore)%20and%20Rs%201%2C025%20million%20(Rs%20102.5%20crore)%20made%20under%20Section%20182%20of%20the%20Act%20(Companies%20Act%2C%202013)%20during%20the%20year%20ended%20March%2031%2C%202023%20and%20March%2031%2C%202022%20respectively%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Bharti%20Airtel%20in%20its%20annual%20report%20for%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20other%20index%20companies%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20list%20only%20sporadically%20reported%20expenditures%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20or%20donations%20to%20political%20parties%20in%20their%20annual%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20instance%2C%20L%26amp%3BT%20and%20Mahindra%20%26amp%3B%20Mahindra%20each%20reported%20making%20political%20donations%20twice%20in%20their%20annual%20reports%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20L%26amp%3BT%20purchased%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2035%20crore%20and%20Rs%2050%20crore%20in%20FY19%20and%20FY20%20respectively%2C%20while%20M%26amp%3BM%20contributed%20Rs%201.02%20crore%20and%20Rs%2023%20crore%20to%20the%20New%20Democratic%20Electoral%20Trust%20in%20FY19%20and%20FY20%2C%20respectively.%20Neither%20company%20mentioned%20any%20other%20political%20donations%20or%20electoral%20bond%20purchases%20in%20subsequent%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20company%20purchased%20electoral%20bonds%20for%20Rs%2050%20crore%20and%20issued%20the%20same%20to%20political%20parties%20as%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20political%20contribution%2C%E2%80%9D%20L%26amp%3BT%20said%20in%20its%20annual%20report%20for%202019-20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETata%20Steel%2C%20which%20disclosed%20a%20donation%20of%20Rs%20175%20crore%20to%20an%20electoral%20trust%20in%20its%202018-19%20annual%20report%2C%20is%20not%20listed%20in%20the%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20database%20of%20companies%20that%20bought%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20business%20daily%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20five%20other%20index%20companies%20reported%20donations%20to%20political%20parties%20only%20once%20in%20the%20past%20five%20financial%20years%3A%20UltraTech%20Cement%20(Rs%2023%20crore%20in%20FY19)%2C%20Bajaj%20Finance%20(Rs%2020%20crore%20in%20FY20)%2C%20Maruti%20Suzuki%20(Rs%2020%20crore%20in%20FY23)%2C%20and%20Tech%20Mahindra%20(Rs%2015%20crore%20in%20FY20).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESun%20Pharmaceuticals%2C%20despite%20being%20recorded%20as%20purchasing%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2031.5%20crore%20since%20FY19%2C%20as%20per%20the%20Election%20Commission%20data%2C%20did%20not%20disclose%20this%20or%20any%20other%20political%20contributions%20in%20its%20annual%20reports%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20Instead%2C%20it%20only%20lists%20expenses%20on%20donations%20without%20detailing%20their%20breakdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711178927000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F14185439%2Fcoins-gebbaa9855_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fonly-eight-of-30-sensex-companies-disclosed-political-donations-in-past-five-fiscals-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Collectively%2C%20these%20companies%20spent%20Rs%20628%20crore%20on%20political%20contributions%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fonly-eight-of-30-sensex-companies-disclosed-political-donations-in-past-five-fiscals-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22BJP%20Got%2093%25%20of%20Bonds%20Before%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20Polls%2C%20Congress%203.2%25%2C%20MK%20Jalan%20Top%20Donor%20to%20Parties%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F23121604%2Fimage-2000.png%5C%22%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKolkata-based%20industrialist%20Mahendra%20Kumar%20Jalan%E2%80%99s%20firms%20and%20Hyderabad-based%20Megha%20Engineering%20and%20Infrastructure%20Limited%20were%20the%20top%20donors%20to%20political%20parties%20ahead%20of%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EReal%20estate%20conglomerate%20DLF%20group%20(DLF%20Commercial%20Developers%20Limited%20and%20DLF%20Luxury%20Homes%20Limited)%20gave%20Rs%2025%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP%20before%20the%20elections.%20They%20had%20been%20under%20a%20cloud%20for%20a%20deal%20with%20former%20Congress%20president%20Sonia%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20son-in-law%20Robert%20Vadra%E2%80%99s%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPiramal%20Group%2C%20in%20which%20Reliance%E2%80%99s%20Mukesh%20Ambani%E2%80%99s%20son-in-law%20Anand%20Piramal%20is%20a%20director%2C%20donated%20to%20both%20Congress%20and%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWelspun%20Enterprises-firm%20linked%20to%20Adani%20donated%20to%20Congress%20before%20the%202019%20elections.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHyderabad-based%20firms%2C%20including%20Dr%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%2C%20were%20top%20donors%20to%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKolkata-%20and%20Maharashtra-based%20firms%20were%20top%20donors%20to%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%2C%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%2C%20and%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Between%20April%2012%20and%20May%2010%2C%202019%2C%2013%20political%20parties%20received%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%202%2C902.87%20crore%20in%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20of%20which%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20alone%20received%20Rs%202%2C719.32%20crore%20or%2093%25%20of%20the%20total%20donations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20parties%20who%20received%20bonds%20included%20the%20Congress%20that%20received%20just%203.2%25%20or%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%2095.29%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKolkata-based%20industrialist%20Mahendra%20Kumar%20Jalan%E2%80%99s%20firms%20and%20Hyderabad-based%20Megha%20Engineering%20and%20Infrastructure%20Limited%20(MEIL)%20were%20the%20top%20donors%20to%20political%20parties%20ahead%20of%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20data%20released%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20on%20March%2021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwho-were-the-top-buyers-of-electoral-bonds-paying%5C%22%3Ehas%20revealed.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20All%20India%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%20received%20Rs%2036.2%20crore%2C%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20received%20Rs%2013.6%20crore%2C%20the%20Sama